OverTheWire Bandit – Level 29 → Level 30

Level Goal
A git repository is available at:
 ssh://bandit29-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org/home/bandit29-git/repo via port 2220.
The password for user bandit29-git is the same as the password for bandit29.

Commands used
git clone
ls
cat

Steps
SSH into the Bandit server.
Use the password for bandit29 to connect as user bandit29-git:
  ssh bandit29-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
Clone the git repository at /home/bandit29-git/repo:
  git clone ssh://bandit29-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:2220/home/bandit29-git/repo
Change into the cloned repo directory:
  cd repo
List files and examine their contents to locate the password for bandit30:
  ls -la
  cat <file-containing-password>

Result
Successfully obtained the password for bandit30 from inside the cloned git repository.

What I Learned
How to clone and explore remote git repositories over SSH with custom ports.
Practical use of git clone in CTF environments.
How sensitive data can be hidden inside git repos during security challenges.
